The African National Congress in KwaZulu-Natal denies being indecisive on the matter of embattled eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal denies it's being indecisive when it comes to finalising eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede's future. The party said come next week, Gumede's fate will be sealed once and for all. The ANC on Tuesday again extended Gumede's leave of absence. READ: ANC extends Zandile Gumede's leave of absence She’s facing fraud and corruption charges over a R208-million Durban Solid Waste tender. “There won’t be a further extension of the leave of absence," said KZN ANC secretary, Mdumiseni Ntuli. "I’m quite certain that when the PEC convenes this coming weekend, it will take a decisive decision on how to move forward.” EXCLUSIVE: eThekwini mayor breaks her silence Ntuli's denying the party is scared of and divided over Gumede. “Anybody who is saying the PEC is divided is really speculating. We had a very united approach," he said. The embattled mayor's supporters are rejecting the party’s decision to extend her leave. Gumede’s due back in court on Thursday. The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal has decided to extend Gumede's leave of absence.